OL,3,CMum accused of cocaine abuse prior to
OL,4,Ccarbon monoxide poisoning diagnosis
OL,6,FNumerous doctors had suspected she was
OL,7,Fregularly taking cocaine, despite Sue
OL,8,Fnever having touched the substance,
OL,9,Fwith other specialists diagnosing her
OL,10,Fwith dementia, despite Sue, from Sale
OL,11,Fin Cheshire, being in her mid-30s at
OL,12,Fthe time.
OL,14,FA routine check by a gas engineer from
OL,15,FBritish Gas found that Sue and her
OL,16,Fyoung son Josh, who was six at the
OL,17,Ftime, were slowly poisoned by carbon
OL,18,Fmonoxide leaking from a badly-fitted
OL,19,Fboiler in their new-build home.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
